description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Post of Healthcare Assistant&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: Band 2/3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen at Woking and Sam Beare Hospice for a Healthcare Assistant to join our Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our patients have life limiting conditions and may be with us for symptom control, terminal end of life care or respite care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a caring and compassionate Healthcare Assistant who is looking to develop their knowledge and skills within a palliative care setting. Whilst experience of palliative care is desirable it is not essential as we can offer support through our training and development programme. Excellent communication skills and the ability to liaise with patients and staff at all levels are, however, essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss this role further or arrange an informal visit , please contact Naomi Langridge (Ward Manager) on 01483 881750.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Woking and Sam Beare Hospiceis a regional charity organisation working closely with itsNHS partners to provide excellent care to patients and their families. Operating from a bespoke building in Goldsworth Park in Woking, the Charity provides inpatient and community services across North West Surrey. Goldsworth Park is close to all major road networks and the Hospice offers ample free car parking.&lt;/p&gt;
